==Swedish==

===Noun===
'''Blatte''' ['blàt:ɛ]
# a derogatory term for a dark-haired person from the Middle East, South America, Africa and to some degree from the Balkans. 

===Etymology===
The word probably originated from a Swedish slang term for "ridiculous person." The use of the term has to some degree shifted to one of self description for above mentioned group of immigrants, including a strong suggestion of segregation and discrimination from ethnic Swedes.

